article.description: Hammonds, Long Beach St. top Cal State-Northridge
article.headline: Hammonds, Long Beach St. top Cal State-Northridge
article.linkText: Hammonds, Long Beach St. top Cal State-Northridge
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Travis Hammonds scored 11 of his season-high 16 points in the final 5:45, and senior David Samuels grabbed a career-high 16 rebounds to help Long Beach State beat Cal State-Northridge 64-58 on Saturday night. Mike Caffey had 14 points and five assists for Long Beach State (10-11, 4-1 Big West) and Tyler Lamb scored 10 with four steals. Caffey made 1 of 2 free throws with 27 seconds left to give the 49ers a 61-55 lead. Six seconds later Aaron Parks made a 3 to pull Northridge (6-15, 2-4) within three, but the Matadors wouldn't score again. Northridge made just 5 of 24 (20.8 percent) field goals and committed 11 turnovers in the first half. Long Beach State led 28-18 at halftime. Stephen Maxwell had 18 points and eight rebounds to lead Northridge, which shot 27.8 percent overall and made just 5 of 17 from 3-point range.
